        <div id="post" id='post-25886'> 
        <h2 class="c_title"><a href="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/2011/12/peppermint-dark-hot-chocolate-mix/" title="Peppermint Dark Hot Chocolate Mix">Peppermint Dark Hot Chocolate Mix</a></h2>
        
       
       
        <span class="date">December 01, 2011<br /></span>
        
                <p id="content"><h3><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.ingredientsinc.net/2011/12/peppermint-dark-hot-chocolate-mix/redo3-jpg-reduced/');"  href="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/2011/12/peppermint-dark-hot-chocolate-mix/redo3-jpg-reduced/" rel="attachment wp-att-25887"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-25887" title="redo3.jpg reduced" src="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/redo3.jpg-reduced.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="540" /></a></h3>
<h3>Okay&#8230;my kids are obsessed with Peppermint Hot Chocolate. The past few weeks we have been visiting <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.starbucks.com/');"  href="http://www.starbucks.com/">Starbucks</a> more than often to savor their craving. Since I have been working on my Christmas list, I decided to create my own homemade version of Peppermint Dark Hot Chocolate Mix that will make the perfect holiday food gift. I used dark chocolate instead of milk or semisweet chocolate, but feel free to use your favorite. It has been said to lower blood pressure, work as a powerful antioxidant and even help release endorphins to boost your mood. It&#8217;s super easy and inexpensive to make, and everyone loves it.</h3>
<p><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.ingredientsinc.net/2011/12/peppermint-dark-hot-chocolate-mix/image-leigh-hot-cooa/');"  href="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/2011/12/peppermint-dark-hot-chocolate-mix/image-leigh-hot-cooa/" rel="attachment wp-att-25912"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-25912" title="Image leigh hot cooa" src="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Image-leigh-hot-cooa.jpg" alt="" width="345" height="460" /></a></p>
</p>
        <div class="hrecipe">
        <h2 class="fn">Peppermint Dark Hot Chocolate Mix</h2>
            <img width="360" height="540" src="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/redo3.jpg-reduced.jpg" class="photo wp-post-image" alt="redo3.jpg reduced" title="redo3.jpg reduced" style="display: none;" /><div>
    <span class="contant_c">Prep:</span>
    <span class="main_contant_c preptime">	    <span class="value-title" title="PT15M"></span>15 minutes</span>
</div><div>
    <span class="contant_c">Yield:</span>
    <span class="main_contant_c yield">1 Gift</span>
</div><div class="content_header">Ingredients</div>
<div class="main_contant_c"><span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1  cup</span> <span class="name"> dark chocolate cocoa powder</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1  cup</span> <span class="name"> granulated sugar</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1  cup</span> <span class="name"> powdered milk</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1/4  teaspoon</span> <span class="name"> sea salt</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1/2  cup</span> <span class="name"> dark chocolate chips</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1/2  cup</span> <span class="name"> miniature marshmallow</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">10 small peppermint sticks, chopped about 1/4  cup</span> <span class="name"></span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount" style="position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; clip: auto; overflow: hidden;">1</span> <span class="name">Peppermint for garnish</span></span></div><div class="content_header">Preparation</div>
<div class="main_contant_c instructions">1. Layer first 7 ingredients in a 1 quart jar.<br />
<br />
2. Add a ribbon and a tie a card and write the following:<br />
<br />
Mix contents in a large bowl. For each serving, place 1/3 cup cocoa mix in a mug with 1 cup boiling water or skim milk and garnish with peppermint, if desired. Store remaining mix in an airtight container for up to 2 weeks.</div><br>
<div class='zl-recipe-link'> <a class='small-butn-link' href='javascript:void(0);' onmouseup='getZRecipe(this, "ingredientsinc", ""); return false;' title='Add this recipe to your ZipList, where you can store all of your favorite web recipes in one place and easily add ingredients to your shopping list.'><span>Add this recipe to ZipList!</span></a> </div>
		</div>
